    "introduction": "Cold Rolling is performed after Hot Rolling to further reduce the thickness of stainless steel at room temperature. It provides improved dimensional accuracy, superior surface finish, and enhanced mechanical properties.",
    "purpose": "The primary objective of Cold Rolling is to produce stainless steel strips and coils with precise dimensions and excellent surface quality suitable for demanding industrial applications.",
    "workingPrinciple": "Hot rolled coils are passed through a series of rollers at room temperature. Controlled rolling pressure reduces the thickness while increasing the material's strength and improving surface finish.",
